    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Oh Kate, re: the Old 97s, you&#8217;re definitely not alone!  <>BIG<> fan here.</></>That&#8217;s great to know, Whitney!  Thank you.</></>And no, Wendy, you&#8217;re not naive.  &#8220;Jar&#8221; is not a normal term of measurement!  As I noted above, just below the photograph, the traditional way of making this cake calls for the ingredients to be measured in little glass yogurt jars.  (In France, that&#8217;s how many yogurts are packaged.)  For our purposes in the States (or in other places where yogurt doesn&#8217;t come in cute little jars), know that <>1 jar equals about 1/2 cup<>.  So 3 jars of flour is 1 1/2 cups.</p>
    </div>

