      <p>I just made the almond meal version of this cake &#8212; after craving for some simple recipe that didn&#8217;t need frosting, room-temperature butter, or my KitchenAid (which needed a break). It came together in minutes, and it finished baking in the time it took me to clean the kitchen tonight! It has such an intriguing taste with the almond meal: very subtle, not sugary at all, rich-tasting without being full-fat. The texture was pleasing (with three eggs, it better!) It&#8217;s a perfect breakfast cake. I can&#8217;t wait to eat some more tomorrow morning! Thanks for the recipe.</p>
