    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2004/08/slow-roasting/#comment-348"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-04-28T15:43:00-04:00">Tuesday, April 28, 2009 at 3:43 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Anonymous, I think a 9-inch springform pan should work, but I worry about some of batter seeping out the edges of the base.  This cake batter isn&#8217;t terribly thick &#8211; only moderately so &#8211; so it really might leak out a little bit.  If you have some parchment paper, you could try lining the pan with that.  It might help.</p>
    </div>

