  <li id="comment-397" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2004/08/slow-roasting/#comment-397"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-01-15T02:04:16-05:00">Sunday, January 15, 2012 at 2:04 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Sarah, sadly, I wish I had written this recipe differently! I think the problem is the varying size and juiciness of lemons. The amount of juice is different in every lemon, so calling for the juice of two lemons is a silly way to measure. I&#39;m sorry about that. I put a newer version of this recipe in my book, and there, I call for 1/4 cup of lemon juice. That, mixed with 1/4 cup of powdered sugar, should be perfect.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
