    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>This recipe is now the first one in my recipe book, as of the last two years. I found your book in a used book store and couldn&#39;t put it down &#8211; every single thing I&#39;ve tried is fabulous! And like you, this cake has become intertwined with my love life. I made this cake while studying abroad in Greece, borrowing a friends&#39; oven since my apartment was only equipped with a mini fridge and hot plate. The morning after serving it at our first school potluck, I came home to discover an oven had been delivered to my kitchen. <br />I made it several weeks later and was nearly hired to make several more for my new favorite tapas bar. After their chef tried it, we started spending every day together sharing wine and food. The &#8220;Winning Hearts and Minds&#8221; cake sealed the deal. And let me just say, Greece was the perfect environment for this cake. Fresh picked lemons, greek yogurt, olive oil&#8230; Truly the most indulgent three months of my life. <br />Thank you so much for all your inspired recipes and musings.</p>
