  <li id="comment-409" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Mary</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2004/08/slow-roasting/#comment-409"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-10-05T16:59:15-04:00">Friday, October 5, 2012 at 4:59 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Made the cake last night for parents&#39; anniversary and they loved it.  I doubled the recipe &#038; did half as cupcakes.  The cupcakes came out deliciously; a bit denser and darker with more chew.  Because I doubled, I did 3 jars almond flour &#038; 3 jars regular &#8211; it really adds a nice subtle flavor.  I glazed and covered the cake after ~45 mins (before it was completely cool) and I think the steam softened the cake &#8211; it&#39;s so soft, moist, and delicious!</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
