    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Thank you so much for this recipe. NO MORE MEASURING CUPS TO WASH! My family LOVES this cake and always request that I make it. I use 2 teaspoons of lemon extract instead of the zest, and a bit of vanilla sugar. I also top it with sliced almonds and my god&#8230; it is so addictive. It takes much longer than 35 minutes to bake in my oven (and I use a 9 inch round pan), probably close to 45 minutes. But this could be because my jar of yogurt is 2/3 cup not 1/2 cup. I also made it in a 9&#215;13 pan with great results. </p>
    </div>

