    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2004/08/slow-roasting/#comment-423"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-03-30T03:56:52-04:00">Sunday, March 30, 2014 at 3:56 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Anonymous, I can&#39;t say for sure what went wrong with your cake, but large air holes are often the result of overmixing. And as for the density issue, I wonder if your oven temperature is off and running too cool? Or if your baking powder is old and not working well? Wish I could give you a more definitive answer.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-424" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2004/08/slow-roasting/#comment-424"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-10-08T01:55:51-04:00">Wednesday, October 8, 2014 at 1:55 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I made this cake and it was TO DIE FOR!!!!!!the lemon flavor it wonderful .  My boyfriend loves chocolate frosting and I thought it wouldn&#39;t taste good but it was it hit!!!! so now when I make it I used chocolate frosting and I make it into cupcakes </p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
