      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-56279" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.instagram.com/tian.yen" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Tian</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2004/08/slow-roasting/#comment-56279"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-07-26T18:38:50-04:00">Tuesday, July 26, 2016 at 6:38 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Thanks for this recipe.  I made it with two thirds almond meal and the rest flour.  It had a chewiness, and I think I would prefer more tenderness, no almond meal next time.</p>
<p>I also reduced the sugar by a quarter and it was sweet enough for us.</p>
<p>I think the amount of oil can also be cut down by a quarter.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-58579" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Kris</cite></div>
